WireGuard Installation Guide
This guide explains how to download and install WireGuard on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems in a simple step-by-step format.

Things You Need Before Starting
•	Laptop or desktop computer
•	Internet connection
•	WireGuard application
•	VPN configuration file (.conf) from the lecturer or server administrator

A. Download the WireGuard App
1.	Open your web browser.
2.	Go to the official WireGuard website https://www.wireguard.com/install/
3.	Choose your operating system: Windows, macOS, or Linux.



4.	Download the installer or follow the installation instructions for your system.


B. Install WireGuard on Windows
1.	Open the downloaded WireGuard installer file.

2.	If Windows asks for permission, click Yes.
3.	Follow the installation wizard.
4.	Click Install.
5.	Wait for the installation to finish.

 


6.	Open the WireGuard application.
7.	To connect to a VPN, click ‘Import tunnel(s) from file’.


8.	Select your .conf configuration file.
9.	Click Activate to start the VPN.

C. Install WireGuard on macOS
1. 	Go to the downloads and select the exe. File that you downloaded.
2. 	Click Get or Install.
3. Open the WireGuard application after installation.
4. Click ‘Import tunnel(s) from file’.
5. Choose your .conf VPN configuration file that you downloaded from the website. 
6. Click Activate to connect.







D. Install WireGuard on Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)
1.	Open Terminal.

2.	Update package list using:
 sudo apt update
3.	Install WireGuard using: 
sudo apt install wireguard -y

4.	Check installation using: wg –version

5.	To start WireGuard later, use your VPN configuration file.


5. Understanding the Configuration File
•	A WireGuard VPN connection requires a .conf file.
•	This file contains VPN settings, keys, and server information.
•	Each student or user should have their own unique configuration file.
•	Do not share private keys with others.


6. Example WireGuard Configuration
•	[Interface]
•	PrivateKey = your_private_key
•	Address = 10.0.0.4/24
•	
•	[Peer]
•	PublicKey = server_public_key
•	Endpoint = server_public_ip:51820
•	AllowedIPs = 10.0.0.0/24



